---
import ServicePage from "../layouts/ServicePage.astro";
---

<ServicePage
  title="Privacy Policy | Upper Cumberland Well Pump"
  description="How Upper Cumberland Well Pump collects, uses, shares and retains information submitted through its well-service request forms."
  path="/privacy-policy/"
  h1="Privacy Policy"
  crumbs={[
    { name: "Home", path: "/" },
    { name: "Privacy Policy", path: "/privacy-policy/" },
  ]}
  isService={false}
  defaultService=""
  relatedLinks={[
    { label: "Terms of Use", href: "/terms/" },
    { label: "Referral Disclosure", href: "/referral-disclosure/" },
    { label: "Contact", href: "/contact/" },
  ]}
>
  <p><em>Last updated: July 2026</em></p>

  <h2>Information We Collect</h2>
  <p>
    When you submit a service request, we collect what you provide: name, phone number, email, city
    or county, optional property location, the service and symptom selections you make, your problem
    description and any photos you choose to attach. The site may also collect standard technical
    data (such as pages visited) through analytics, when analytics is enabled.
  </p>

  <h2>How We Use It</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>To review and route your service request.</li>
    <li>
      To share the request, with your consent, with an independent local well-service provider for
      the purpose of responding to your inquiry.
    </li>
    <li>To contact you about your request.</li>
    <li>To maintain records of requests, including the consent you gave and when.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>What We Do Not Do</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>We do not sell general marketing lists of visitor information.</li>
    <li>
      We do not send your name, phone, email, address or problem description to analytics services.
    </li>
    <li>
      We do not require an account or store payment information — the website takes no payments.
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Sharing</h2>
  <p>
    Request details are shared with independent providers only for responding to your inquiry, and
    only after you check the consent box. Infrastructure vendors (hosting, spam protection,
    email/webhook delivery, optional storage) process data on our behalf as needed to operate the
    site. We may disclose information if required by law.
  </p>

  <h2>Photos</h2>
  <p>
    Uploaded photos are stored privately, referenced only for your request, and are not published.
    Do not upload photos containing people or sensitive documents.
  </p>

  <h2>Retention and Deletion</h2>
  <p>
    Lead records are retained only as long as needed to operate the referral service and meet
    record-keeping obligations. You may request deletion of your submitted information through the <a
      href="/contact/">contact page</a
    >; include the reference number from your confirmation if you have it.
  </p>

  <h2>Cookies and Analytics</h2>
  <p>
    The site aims to run with minimal tracking. If analytics is enabled, it is configured for
    aggregate usage measurement (page views, anonymized interactions) rather than identification.
    The Cloudflare Turnstile anti-spam widget on forms sets its own operational cookies per
    Cloudflare's policies.
  </p>

  <h2>Your Choices</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>You can browse the entire site without submitting anything.</li>
    <li>You can decline consent — the request simply will not be sent.</li>
    <li>
      You can request access to or deletion of your submitted data via the <a href="/contact/"
        >contact page</a
      >.
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Changes</h2>
  <p>Material changes to this policy will be posted on this page with an updated date.</p>
</ServicePage>
